4. Write a query to display departments having more than 3 employees.
 SELECT COUNT(*),  D.DNAME FROM ( EMP E INNER JOIN DEPT D ON E.DEPTNO = D.DEPTNO) GROUP BY D.DNAME HAVING COUNT(*) >3;

  COUNT(*) DNAME
---------- --------------
         5 RESEARCH
         6 SALES
  
5. Write a query to display jobs where the maximum salary is greater than 4000.
 SELECT MAX(SAL), JOB FROM EMP GROUP BY JOB HAVING MAX(SAL)>4000;

  MAX(SAL) JOB
---------- ---------
      5000 PRESIDENT

